I’ve been dying to share this with you all… I get asked constantly who I go to for Botox, lip filler, etc, and the answer is @avantemedicalaesthetics! @cosmeticswithmary is a wizard with skin and I wouldn’t trust anyone else with my face. She has had extensive experience with dermatology, being a surgical assistant, and she is not just an injector, she actually practices medicine. I adore her, I’m always thrilled with my results, and she keeps me looking natural- never overdone. Watch as I get Botox and lip filler and share the healing with you! This is an appreciation post for Nix, my first-born sweetie boy. I can’t believe how big he is and how fast time has gone by. 4.5 is a rough age but I’m constantly learning how to be a better parent because of it. I’ll be 36 next month and as I’m getting older, I’m trying to give myself more grace concerning my appearance. Im making sure that my aesthetic choices are for *me* and I don’t have time to care what people might think about them. I wear what I want, when I want. I do my hair and makeup in ways that make me feel good… and some days that’s a full beat with 2 pairs of lashes and some days that’s no makeup at all. I’ve really tried to take care of my skin lately and I realized I don’t know that I’ve ever posted a completely naked face with no filter… so hi hello. Enjoy my face in its natural state. Scars and all. Give yourself grace!

Needless to say, we can’t wait to return to the Magic Kingdom.

We took on a massive project in September and decided to completely gut our Primary Bathroom. The tub and shower were too small for either of us to comfortably enjoy and the bathroom was original to the 1992 build. I’ve always dreamed of a black tiled bathroom and designing this was SO much fun. I handpicked everything and even drew up all of the specs myself. I’m so proud of this design! It’s so much more kid and pet friendly now as well, hell the whole family could fit if we wanted to! 🛁 Design tip: paint the inside of your closet for a fun accent and easy way to change things up a bit!

New hair! I was feeling like I needed something a bit brighter and funky, and let me tell you I’m obsessed with the @dangerjonescreative direct dyes! ❤️‍🔥💥🔥

Process:
I started by touching up my roots as usual with @schwarzkopfusa Igora Royal 8-77 with 0-77 and 20v, and added 2 blocks of 3-65 with 0-77 and 10v, one slice of bleach in my bangs, and some sliced balayage pieces throughout the rest. After that process, on dry hair, I used @dangerjonescreative Burnout, Simpatico and Starrider deposited over all of that in alternating brick-layed blocking, with the top cat eye section in burnout. Someone told me I look like a phoenix and I love it! 

Side note: I just switched to the @anastasiabeverlyhills foundation and it’s honestly incredible, so lightweight, has buildable flawless coverage, and wears perfectly all day. I’m blown away.
